{
  "texts": [
    "Compared to word-based tokenisation, this leads to a smaller vocabulary, and out-of-vocabulary tokens will be less frequent.",
    "On the other hand, the information content per token is much smaller (unless for ideogram-based languages), and the token sequences to be processed by the model are much longer, thus limiting the maximum allowable text length.",
    "• Subword-based tokenisation combines the advantages of the previous approaches by retaining frequent words and splitting rarer words into subwords (e.g.",
    "\"cats\" into \"cat\" +\"s\", prefixes and suffixes).",
    "Compared to word-based tokenisation, the vocabulary size is much smaller, as information is shared across different words."
  ]
}